  "text": "The Kubernetes admission webhook processing chain is implemented through a coordinated system of components:\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nThe admission webhook processing chain is a multi-layered system implemented in the kubernetes/kubernetes and kubernetes/api repositories. The chain processes both mutating webhooks (that can modify objects) and validating webhooks (that only validate objects).\n\n## Core Components\n\n### 1. WebhookAccessor Abstraction Layer\nThe WebhookAccessor interface (defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/accessors.go`) provides a unified abstraction for accessing both MutatingWebhook and ValidatingWebhook objects. This interface implements the methods needed to support matching against webhook predicates, including GetUID, GetConfigurationName, GetRESTClient, GetCompiledMatcher, and various getter methods for webhook configuration fields.\n\nTwo concrete implementations are provided:\n- `mutatingWebhookAccessor`: Wraps v1.MutatingWebhook objects\n- `validatingWebhookAccessor`: Wraps v1.ValidatingWebhook objects\n\nBoth are instantiated via factory functions `NewMutatingWebhookAccessor` and `NewValidatingWebhookAccessor` respectively.\n\n### 2. Generic Webhook Dispatcher\nThe generic webhook dispatcher (in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/webhook.go`) is the abstract admission plugin that provides the infrastructure for both mutating and validating webhooks. The `Webhook` struct handles:\n- Webhook configuration management through a `sourceFactory`\n- Client connection management via `ClientManager`\n- Predicate matching (namespace and object selectors)\n- Delegation to specific mutating or validating dispatchers\n\nThe dispatcher interfaces are defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/interfaces.go`, including the `Dispatcher` interface that handles actual webhook invocation.\n\n### 3. Mutating Webhook Dispatcher with Reinvocation Logic\nThe mutating webhook dispatcher (in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/dispatcher.go`) implements the `Dispatcher` interface and processes mutating webhooks sequentially. It includes sophisticated reinvocation logic:\n\n- Tracks previously invoked webhooks via `webhookReinvokeContext`\n- Manages object mutations across multiple webhook invocations\n- Detects when in-tree plugins have mutated the object and triggers webhook reinvocation\n- Maintains state about which webhooks have been invoked and should be reinvoked\n\nThe reinvocation context (in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/reinvocationcontext.go`) is a key component that:\n- Tracks the last webhook output to detect changes\n- Maintains sets of previously invoked reinvocable webhooks\n- Manages which webhooks need to be reinvoked based on object mutations\n\nThe mutating webhook plugin (in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/plugin.go`) registers itself as \"MutatingAdmissionWebhook\" and implements the admission.MutationInterface.\n\n### 4. Validating Webhook Dispatcher with Parallel Dispatch\nThe validating webhook dispatcher (in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/dispatcher.go`) processes validating webhooks in parallel for improved performance. Key features:\n\n- Constructs all necessary versions needed for webhook calls upfront\n- Caches versioned attributes to avoid redundant conversions\n- Spawns goroutines for each webhook invocation in parallel\n- Aggregates errors from all webhooks\n- Includes panic recovery mechanisms for webhook failures\n\nThe validating webhook plugin (in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/plugin.go`) registers itself as \"ValidatingAdmissionWebhook\" and implements the admission.ValidationInterface.\n\n### 5. Configuration Management\nTwo configuration managers handle the dynamic loading and watching of webhook configurations:\n\n- `mutatingWebhookConfigurationManager` (in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/mutating_webhook_manager.go`) manages MutatingWebhookConfiguration objects using informers and creates mutating webhook accessors\n- `validatingWebhookConfigurationManager` (in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/validating_webhook_manager.go`) manages ValidatingWebhookConfiguration objects similarly\n\nBoth managers implement the `generic.Source` interface and use lazy evaluation with cache invalidation on updates.\n\n### 6. API Type Definitions\nThe webhook configuration types are defined in `admissionregistration/v1/types.go` in the kubernetes-api repository:\n\n- `MutatingWebhookConfiguration`: Cluster-scoped resource containing a list of MutatingWebhook definitions\n- `ValidatingWebhookConfiguration`: Cluster-scoped resource containing a list of ValidatingWebhook definitions\n- `MutatingWebhook`: Individual webhook configuration with name, client config, rules, and failure policy\n- `ValidatingWebhook`: Individual webhook configuration for validation-only purposes\n\nThese types are registered in `admissionregistration/v1/register.go`.\n\n## Processing Chain Flow\n\n1. When a request arrives, the admission system invokes either the mutating or validating webhook plugin\n2. The plugin delegates to the generic Webhook's Dispatch method\n3. The generic webhook queries the configuration manager for active webhooks (wrapped as WebhookAccessor)\n4. For each webhook, it evaluates predicates (rules, namespaceSelector, objectSelector) via ShouldCallHook\n5. Matching webhooks are passed to the dispatcher (mutating or validating)\n6. For mutating webhooks: Sequential processing with reinvocation logic tracks mutations\n7. For validating webhooks: Parallel processing for performance with error aggregation\n8. The final decision (allow/deny) and any mutations are returned to the API server\n\nThis architecture provides a flexible, extensible, and performant framework for dynamic admission webhooks in Kubernetes."
